info.name: Black Dal Fry
info.description: Serves 1 | Dal fry is classic punjabi style dal made with whole black gram lentils [urad dal] slow cooked with tomatoes, ginger, garlic, garam masala, finished with lots of butter & heavy cream. One of the distinguishing flavors in dal bukhara is its pronounced smokiness which sets the taste of this dal apart from other traditional black urad lentil preparations like dal makhani and dal maharani.

info.name: Dal Makhani
info.description:
Serves 1 | Creamy and buttery dal makhani is one of indias most loved dal!

this dal has whole black lentils cooked with butter and cream and simmered on low heat for that unique flavor. It tastes best with garlic naan!

info.name: Dal Yellow

info.name: Kadai Paneer

info.name: Shahi Paneer
info.description: Serves 1 | Shahi paneer - this is mughalai paneer recipe. Soft paneer pieces are simmered in rich, creamy, aromatic and flavorful white gravy.

info.name: Mattar Paneer
info.description: Serves 1 | Matter paneer recipe is a popular Indian curry dish, made with green peas with paneer [Indian cottage cheese] in a base of onions, tomatoes, cashews, spices and herbs. The recipe hails from the versatile northern Indian cuisine.

info.name: Paneer Do Pyaza
info.description: Serves 1 | Paneer do pyaza is a rich, creamy curry of soft succulent paneer and plenty of onions in a wonderful medley of spices, herbs and tomatoes..

info.name: Paneer Butter Masala

info.name: Paneer Hariyali Tikka
info.description: Serves 1 | Paneer hariyali tikka a simple green herb based paneer recipe which is prepared very similar to the other tikka recipes or paneer tikka recipe. It is an ideal party starter or evening snack with the goodness of paneer and aroma of pudina and coriander.

info.name: Paneer Malai Tikka
info.description: Serves 1 | Paneer malai tikka the traditional tikka recipes which are known for its spicy flavours, malai tikka is mild and creamy in taste. It is an excellent party starter or an appetiser recipe which can also be served as a side to roti and chapati meal.

info.name: Paneer Achari Tikka
info.description: Serves 1 | It is a robust variation of the classic paneer tikka where the cottage cheese cubes are flavored with marination of thick curd, pickling spices and seasonings.

info.name: Afghani Masala Soya Chaap
info.description: Serves 1 | Afghani malai chaap tikka is a great and unique recipe with a great taste. Its like a bag full of flavors in our mouth. Soya chaaps are nothing but made out of soy proteins. It is great alternate option to meat when one is a vegetarian..

info.name: Mushroom Chilli
info.description: Serves 1 | A popular indo chinese starter recipe or a street food snack prepared with deep fried mushroom and chilli based sauce. It is almost similar to any indo chinese chilli recipe, prepared with button mushrooms..

info.name: Honey Chilli Cauliflower
info.description: Serves 1 | Honey chilli cauliflower is a famous indo-chinese recipe dipped in sauces and deep fried coated with batter. It is a delicious starter for any occasion and can be prepared in no time. Sesame seeds and honey on top is the most drooling part of this dish which make it perfect to go. This can be made dry or with some gravy by adding corn flour slurry to it.

info.name: Crispy Channa
info.description: Serves 1 | Crunchy crispy chickpeas is a very chatpata (spicy), kurkura (crunchy) north indian style snack, which is well-liked for its chatpata aftertaste. This is a great snack to munch on, and they are so addictive that youll keep on chomping them.

info.name: Crispy Corn
info.description:
Serves 1 | Crispy corn is a crunchy, tasty vegetarian snack. Loaded with the indian-chinese fusion flavors...

bonus: if you are looking for a vegetarian + tasty snack to feed the crowd then this crispy corn recipe is worth bookmarking.

info.name: Honey Chilli Potato
